{"questionId":"13988","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Let&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( x \\right) = \\frac{{16}}{x}\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>16</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>. The line <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"L\">\n  <mi>L</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;is tangent to the graph of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n</math></span> at&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = 8\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>8</mn>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"L\">\n  <mi>L</mi>\n</math></span> can be expressed in the form <em><strong>r</strong></em>&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = \\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  8 \\\\   2  \\end{array}} \\right) + t\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>8</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span><em><strong>u</strong></em>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The direction vector of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = x\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> is&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  1 \\\\   1  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence, write down <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{f^{ - 1}}\\left( x \\right)\"> <mrow> <msup> <mi>f</mi> <mrow> <mo>−</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </msup> </mrow> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"font-family:Verdana , sans-serif;font-size:10.5pt;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{f^{ - 1}}\\left( x \\right) = \\frac{{16}}{x}\"> <mrow> <msup> <mi>f</mi> <mrow> <mo>−</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </msup> </mrow> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>16</mn> </mrow> <mi>x</mi> </mfrac> </math></span>&nbsp; (accept&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = \\frac{{16}}{x}\"> <mi>y</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>16</mn> </mrow> <mi>x</mi> </mfrac> </math></span>, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{16}}{x}\"> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>16</mn> </mrow> <mi>x</mi> </mfrac> </math></span>)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</span><strong style=\"font-family:Verdana , sans-serif;font-size:10.5pt;\"><em>A1 N1</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A0</strong></em> in part (ii) if part (i) is incorrect.<br>Award <em><strong>A0</strong></em> in part (ii) if the candidate has found <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{f^{ - 1}}\\left( x \\right) = \\frac{{16}}{x}\"> <mrow> <msup> <mi>f</mi> <mrow> <mo>−</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </msup> </mrow> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>16</mn> </mrow> <mi>x</mi> </mfrac> </math></span> by interchanging <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"> <mi>x</mi> </math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\"> <mi>y</mi> </math></span>.</p>\n<p><strong><em><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Verdana' , sans-serif;color:black;\">[1 mark]</span></em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13988","referenceCode":"19M.2.SL.TZ1.S_9d.ii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence, write down f − 1 ( x ) .","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.4—Tangents and normal"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}